results.name: Table read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) = number of factorizations of (n,k) into pairs (i,j) with i,j>=1, not both 1.
comment: The rule of building products is (a,b)*(x,y) = (a*x,b*y).
The number of divisors of (n,k) is A143235(n,k)-1, where the subtraction of 1 means that the unit (1,1) is not admitted here. - _R. J. Mathar_, Nov 30 2017
